    <h5>Introduction</h5>
    <p>This website processes personal data for genealogical research purposes in accordance with article 6 first subparagraph point (f) of the <a class="text-primary" href="https://commission.europa.eu/law/law-topic/data-protection/data-protection-eu_en">General Data Protection Regulation</a> (GDPR) as set out in this privacy statement. I distinguish between personal data that I process for the purpose of my genealogical research and personal data that you provide to me yourself when you create a free user account on this website.</p>

    <ol>
        <h4><li>Personal data for the purpose of genealogical research</li></h4>
        <p>I process personal data from public sources (archives, newspapers, websites, etc.), from my own sources or because you or someone else has provided it to me for the purpose of my genealogical research. Visitors have limited access to the data of deceased persons: People who died more than 10 years ago, or people born more than 120 years ago. Members with a user account also have access to:</p>

        <ul>
            <li>data of deceased persons</li>
            <li>(limited) data of living persons to whom they are related in the first or second degree (partner, (step)child, grandchild, parent, grandparent, uncle/aunt)</li>
            <li>own data</li>
        </ul><br />

        <p>Specific personal data (see below) are always protected, even for registered close relatives. You can always request to see your own data collected for my genealogical research, even if you do not have a user account. If you do not want your data to be viewable by registered close relatives, please let me know via the <a class="text-primary" href="https://www.ravenzwaaij.info/tree/ravenzwaaij/message-compose?to=Lars1963&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ravenzwaaij.info%2Fmodule%2F_privacy_footer_%2FPage%2Fravenzwaaij">contact form</a>.</p>

        <h5>Specific and/or sensitive personal data</h5>
        <p>For my genealogical research, I process specific and/or sensitive personal data from public sources (archives, newspapers, websites, etc), from my own sources or because you or someone else has provided it to me. Below is a list of the specific personal data I may process for the purpose of my genealogical research:</p>

        <ul>
            <li>racial or ethnic origin</li>
            <li>political opinions</li>
            <li>religion or belief</li>
            <li>union membership</li>
